Click on the slide show to see this week’s featured properties in New York City:
• In South Park Slope, a two-bedroom, one-and-one-half-bath parlor-floor and garden-level condo in an 8-unit 1910 townhouse. It has two living areas, an open kitchen, a private patio, a washer/dryer and a lower level master suite with a walk-in closet.
• In Chelsea, a one-bedroom, one-bath prewar apartment with fresh finishes in a 16-story corner building.
• In Clinton, a two-bedroom, two-bath condo with impressive volume and a flexible floor plan in a 16-unit prewar conversion.
